.TH MV(1),User Commands,MV(1)

.SH NAME
mv - rename a file

.SH SYNOPSIS
mv source destination

.SH DESCRIPTION
mv renames source to destination using the underlying filesystem rename operation.
Exactly two operands are required.

Only a single source/destination pair is supported.
mv does not copy data between filesystems; source and destination must live on the same filesystem.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
mv: missing file operand - no arguments were given.

mv: missing destination file operand after 'SOURCE' - only a single operand was given.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: Rename issued.

1: No operand was given, or only a source was given.

.SH SEE ALSO
cp(1)
